00:54:30.450 --> 00:54:35.940
&gt;&gt; A lot of those pictures show
the chairs a little [inaudible].

00:54:35.940 --> 00:54:37.240
&gt;&gt; Yes.

00:54:37.240 --> 00:54:39.610
&gt;&gt; Is that how they
originally were intended,

00:54:39.610 --> 00:54:42.500
or why are those little
[inaudible] there?

00:54:42.500 --> 00:54:45.860
&gt;&gt; Yeah, well you know,
we associated casters

00:54:45.860 --> 00:54:47.160
with [inaudible] furniture,

00:54:47.160 --> 00:54:50.530
and a lot of furniture
[inaudible] had casters,

00:54:50.530 --> 00:54:54.300
but the truth is, casters
go back to the 18th century.

00:54:54.300 --> 00:54:56.330
The early ones were
made out of--

00:54:56.330 --> 00:55:01.170
they'd take strips of leather,
and wind them into a circle,

00:55:01.170 --> 00:55:03.250
and they were often
used as casters.

00:55:03.250 --> 00:55:05.560
So there were casters
in the 18th century.

00:55:05.560 --> 00:55:10.170
It's kind of an expensive
detail, and by the 19th century,

00:55:10.170 --> 00:55:14.340
the technology was such that you
could make them less expensive.

00:55:14.340 --> 00:55:18.670
The other reason that they're
so common in the 19th century is

00:55:18.670 --> 00:55:22.290
that by the 19th century, we
began to see central heating,

00:55:22.290 --> 00:55:26.000
and so instead of having to
huddle at the fire all the time,

00:55:26.000 --> 00:55:28.350
you could move the stuff around,
you know, you could put it

00:55:28.350 --> 00:55:31.180
by the fire, you could go near
the window, and it was nice

00:55:31.180 --> 00:55:35.440
to be able to roll the furniture
around, and very convenient,

00:55:35.440 --> 00:55:37.510
and so a lot of the
furniture does have that.

00:55:37.510 --> 00:55:39.910
A lot of them have been removed,
because they're associated

00:55:39.910 --> 00:55:41.600
with Victorian furniture,
but even today,

00:55:41.600 --> 00:55:44.210
lots of furniture has
casters on them too,

00:55:44.210 --> 00:55:46.350
just so that you can
move them around.

00:55:46.350 --> 00:55:48.230
Because furniture
is pretty heavy.

00:55:48.230 --> 00:55:50.970
Yeah. Good question.

